infos.info: From March 18, 1939 issue of Radio Guide: ';Prominent authorities on civic affairs speak on civil service, relief, housing and other important community questions of the day, then submit to query by a forum panel of ten high-school students under the direction of Dr. James G. McDonald. president of the Brooklyn Institute of Arts and Sciences. Each week a new panel is chosen from different New York City high schools.'
